                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14053723" author="hcorg" created="Mon, 7 Jul 2014 14:56:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve suggested adding those macros to config.h on windows, but I&apos;ve got no idea if values of those macros should be static or somehow depended on architecture (does windows works on architecture which would require different values of those macros?)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14053730" author="ben.craig" created="Mon, 7 Jul 2014 15:05:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;You could fix if for the platforms that you care about, and continue to let it error elsewhere.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;i386 and x64 are the main platforms to worry about, with ARM following behind that.  A distant fourth would be IA64.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14053844" author="hcorg" created="Mon, 7 Jul 2014 16:50:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;So what would you say for such patch?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14053892" author="ben.craig" created="Mon, 7 Jul 2014 17:26:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The attached patch looks fine to me (though I haven&apos;t tested).  +1.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When the MSVC + ARM developers complain, they can put the appropriate code behind an _M_ARM guard.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14054136" author="roger.meier" created="Mon, 7 Jul 2014 20:07:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;committed&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
